      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ICEBERG AHEAD (2) jumps from box 2 for the first time after scoring at this track (22.33) in a Grade 5. Has a strong winning record here. Has good speed and a low draw is a big help. Makes plenty of appeal if runs up to latest. POKER NISMO (3) has shown good improvement at her last two starts, rewarded with a win last time at The Gardens over 400m. Smart beginner who should take advantage of the low draw. One of main contenders. HAPPY ETHICS (5) turned in a better run last time to find a minor placing (30.17) at Wentworth Park behind Galba Major in a Grade 5. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. Comes through a solid form race last start. Expected to feature again. SIR TICK (8) warrants respect following a recent placing at big odds.",
